LINE.Text: ONE IN SEVEN EU SHOPPERS BUYING FROM UK WEBSITES AS OF
2019 WOULD STOP PURCHASING CROSS-BORDER IF ADDITIONAL
EUROPE: SHARE OF ONLINE SHOPPERS IN EUROPE CURRENTLY BUYING CROSS-BORDER FROM UK WEBSITES WHO WOULD STOP
BUYING FROM FOREIGN WEBSITES IN CASE OF ADDITIONAL COSTS AFTER CHECKOUT, BY SELECTED COUNTRIES, IN %, JUNE
Definition: additional costs after checkout refer to costs such as customs clearance, extra fees, extra foreign
Survey: based on a survey of 24,258 shoppers in 21 European countries, conducted in June 2019; question asked:
"'Would you continue to buy from foreign websites in the future if there were additional costs to pay after
check-out (custom clearance, extra fees, extra foreign exchange costs, other taxes, etc.)?"
Source: DPD, GfK, October 2019; as cited in the report "The Implications of Brexit for UK and EU B2C E-Commerce
